original: LENFELDT, Leo, Advokat, Malmö, f Malmö 14/12 05, gm Maya Holmström. Studex Malmö 24, jur kand Lund 31. E. o. hovrättsnot 31, tingstjg Oxie o Skytts doms 31—34, bitr jur å G Richters adv.byrå Malmö 34—35, delägadv.fma Lenfeidt & Eriksson sed. 35. Resoffex 26, kapt Träng :s res 41. Led Sv adv.samf, styr.led P N Dahlgrens fastigh.AB, Malmö fastigh.äg.frn, Malmö fastigh.äg:s arb.giv.frn, Sv arm :s resoff frbs Skåneavd. °:LENGQUIST, David. Disponent, Flen, f Oskarshamn 24/11 78. Eft slut skolgång anst s bildhugg. En av gr o deläg Blomstermåla möbelfabr 00, inneh AB Möbelfabr Varia Flen sed. 22. Ordf munie.nmd o vatten- o elvks-styr, led fi komm nmd o styr. Ordf Sv Mö-belind.frb, Sv Tapetser Arb.giv.frb o Sv Kon-torsmöbelfabrik.frb, styr.led Sv Träind.frb o Träind:s branschorganisation.
translated: LENFELDT, Leo, Lawyer, Malmö, b Malmö 14/12 05, m Maya Holmström. Studied in Malmö until 24, graduated in law from Lund in 31. Acting associate judge in 31, district judge in Oxie and Skytts in 31—34, assistant lawyer at G Richter's law office in Malmö in 34—35, co-owner of Lenfeidt & Eriksson since 35. Reserve officer since 26, captain in the Reserves of the Army's Transportation Corps since 41. Member of the Swedish Bar Association, board member of P N Dahlgren's real estate company, Malmö real estate owner, employer representative of Malmö real estate owners, Reserve officer with the Skåne division. °:LENGQUIST, David. Manager, Flen, b Oskarshamn 24/11 78. After completing school, employed as a sculptor. One of the founders and co-owners of Blomstermåla Möbelfabrik since 00, proprietor of AB Möbelfabr Varia Flen since 22. Chairman of the municipal committee and water and electricity control committee, board member of the employers' association in the furniture industry, the Upholsterers' Employment Association, and the Swedish office furniture manufacturers' association, board member of the Swedish Wood Industry Association and its branch organization.
